Sudanese President Supports Korea's Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- The Sudanese government and people are keeping the unforgettable feelings of friendship with the DPRK and there is no change in the feelings and our stand supporting the struggle of the Korean people.
 Sudanese President Omar Hassan Ahmed Al-Bashir said this on November 19 when receiving credentials from DPRK Ambassador to the country O Ul Rok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic and traditional relations between the two countries have been strengthened and developed in the joint struggle against imperialism, the president said, adding that President Kim Il Sung gave a large amount of precious assistance and cooperation to the Sudanese people in their struggle to build a new society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the DPRK for having firmly defended the independent stand and principle under the wise guidance of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il despite the sanctions and pressure of the imperialist allied forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Sudanese people will in the future, too, stand firm on the side of the Korean people and positively support the reunification of Korea, he stressed.

Human Scum's Vandalism under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Ro Jin, chairman of the Seoul District Federation of University Student Councils under the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils, reportedly issued a statement on Dec. 8 to denounce the human scum including the Grand National Party for destroying the graveyard of unconverted long-term prisoners.
 Recalling that on Dec. 5 the hooligans of the wicked conservative organisations including the "Fellowship Society for Special Operatives Dispatched to the North" ruthlessly destroyed the gravestones of unconverted long-term prisoners at the Pogwang Temple in Phaju City, Kyonggi Province and committed thrice-cursed crimes such as pouring paint over wrecks of tombstones and boxes of remains, the statement said this makes even mountains and streams shudder with indignation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Grand National Party and Chosun Ilbo which encouraged gangsters to such vandalism while criticizing the graveyard of unconverted long-term prisoners with slanders and fabrications proved through the current case that they are human scum knowing no manners of human being and a group of beasts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will certainly call human scum to task. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will revenge on the GNP and Chosun Ilbo a thousand fold for manipulating and agitating the case behind the scene.

Probe into Truth behind Murder of Farmer Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- The Committee for Practicing Freedom of the Writers' Association of National Literature of south Korea reportedly held a press conference at the hospital attached to Seoul National University on Dec. 7 at which it strongly demanded the "government" authorities make a thoroughgoing probe into the truth about the murder of farmer Jon Yong Chol.
 At the press conference speakers expressed resentment at the action of the political camp keeping mum about the murder case, far from apologizing for it. They accused the authorities of opening the rice market and enacting the evil law on part-timers which drive the majority to death just to meet the interests of the minority. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The death of farmer Jon is not a simple case of a farmer but a case threatening the death of all the workers and farmers, they said, demanding the authorities properly probe the cause of the murder case and punish those responsible for it without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A statement was read out at the press conference.

Struggle against Expansion of U.S. Military Base Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- A press conference was reportedly held in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Dec. 9 to make a great success in the December 11 grand peace march for checking the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek and achieving peace on the Korean Peninsula. It was sponsored by the All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek.
 At the press conference speakers said that the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek is aimed at realizing the "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. forces in south Korea and laying the foundation for increasing their role. This will bring the south Korean people nothing but the danger of war and only result in the U.S. forces' permanent occupation of south Korea and all sorts of crimes and the destruction of living environment. They vowed to check the expansion of the U.S. military base at the cost of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal to all organizations of south Korea and the world's peace-loving people was published at the press conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At this moment the precious fertile soil on this land is in danger of being destroyed owing to the U.S. moves to expand the base for aggression and war in a bid to hold supremacy, not only the inhabitants in Phyongthaek but all the people who have undergone sufferings due to the U.S. forces' occupation of south Korea for over half a century should rise up in the struggle against the expansion of the U.S. military base, the appeal said.  The appeal called for achieving success in the December 11 grand peace march for checking the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek and realizing peace on the Korean Peninsula for the present.

Japan's Moves for Overseas Expansion Slammed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- Japan is busy with its moves for the retrogressive revision of its present constitution as evidenced by its increased efforts to promote the status of the Defence Agency into that of a ministry and reorganize the Self-Defence Forces (SDF) into regular armed forces, while asserting the importance of the military tie-up with the United States.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today observes in a signed commentary: This indicates that the Japanese reactionaries' moves to round off the legal and institutional mechanism for turning Japan into a military power and realizing its ambition for overseas expansion have reached a full scale phase.
 The news analyst further goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "pacifist constitution" stipulates as a state policy that post-war Japan, a defeated nation, shall never go to a war again nor take part in any military action of such form. Japan should not revise this constitution if it does not want to be called a war state or aggressive state again.
 The retrogressive revision of the constitution, which is being accelerated at a final stage in Japan, is an expression of reckless militarist insanity of the Japanese reactionaries preoccupied by the ambition for overseas expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such moves are being stepped up at the zealous instigation of the United States. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' undisguised moves for the retrogressive revision of the constitution are a danger signal heralding the emergence of a new war state in Asia and the Japanese militarists' start of overseas expansion. 
 The reckless constitutional revision and overseas expansion are leading Japan to destruction. The reactionaries of Japan would be well advised to behave themselves, mindful of this.

Classical Poems and Songs Associated with Home Towns of Great Persons Found out 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- Researchers of the Academy of Social Science of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have found out and arranged classical poems and songs associated with the home towns of President Kim Il Sung, leader Kim Jong Il and anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk, three generals of Mt. Paektu.
 They found out the poems and songs while studying the old names of the native places and data on their beautiful scenery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The poems and songs dated from the period of Koryo Dynasty to the close of Ri Dynasty are rich in content and of high artistic value.
 They include various genres ranging from long poem to sonnet, collection of poems, short lyric poem and folk song, which were created by hundreds of writers including Hong Ryang Ho, Ri Si Hang, Kim Si Sup, Nam I and Kim Jong So famous in their ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are thousands of poems and songs related to Mangyongdae and Pyongyang and hundreds to Mt. Paektu and Hoeryong.
 Typical of them are a poem "Mangyongdae", a long poem "Mt. Paektu", words of songs "Eight Beautiful Views in Hoeryong" and "Song of Osan".
 They extol the natural scenery of the Mangyongdae area as the most beautiful one in the East, Mt. Paektu as ancestral mountain associated with the soul of the nation and the Hoeryong area, north gateway to Korea, associated with stories about bravery displayed by people in battles against foreign invaders as symbol of national defence. The poetical compositions are run through with ardent love for the country and great national pride. 
 The works describe Mangyongdae, Mt. Paektu and Hoeryong as mysterious places permeated with the spirit of the nation and laud their superb landscapes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All this shows that the native places of the three generals of Mt. Paektu have been dear to the Korean people from olden times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The newly discovered poems and songs are works of national treasure in adding luster to the unique national characteristics of Juche-oriented literature and gaining a better understanding of fine cultural heritage of the nation.

New Artificial Bezoar Manufacturing Process Developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- Scientists of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have succeeded in developing new methods of manufacturing artificial bezoar and cultivating chlorella.
 The "Sogyong artificial bezoar manufacturing method" and "cultivation method of chlorella by new organic substances" were awarded the patent of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By the new method, artificial bezoar is made with by-products of live-stock farms. Its production cost is low. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The artificial bezoar made by the new method is similar with the natural one in its ingredients. It is widely used as raw materials for Koryo medicines for its high medicinal virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The method of cultivating chlorella by new organic substances does not need acetic acid in the production of chlorella, while the old method consumes 30 tons of acetic acid per one ton of chlorella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now pharmaceutical and foodstuff factories of the country are producing various kinds of health food and condiment with chlorella produced by the new method.

Korean Students Place First at Recitation Contest in China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 12 (KCNA) -- Korean students Han Jin A and Han Un Ha won the first prizes at a recitation contest of students studying in China which was held in Beijing a few days ago.
 At least 80 foreign students of 28 countries and regions selected at different universities of China participated in the semifinals and over 20 excellent students of at least 10 countries and regions including the DPRK, Thailand, Japan, Germany, Russia, Switzerland, France and the U.S. in the finals.
 Han Jin A and Han Un Ha studying at Dongbei and Liaoning Universities of China recited the prose they prepared and successfully did impromptu recitation of what is given by the jury, combining it with artistic depiction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They placed first with highest marks of the contest and were awarded gold cups, first prizes and honorable certificates. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the jury said: It is great that two Korean students placed first. First places have never been given to students of one country. It is the trait of only Koreans to have high national pride and advance, not giving up anything.
